title: Economic Correlations and Insights Analysis
text:
Project Brief
SQL Project: Economic and Social Analysis of Countries
This SQL-based project provides an in-depth analysis of the economic and social well-being of countries across multiple indicators, including GDP, corruption, cost of living, tourism, and unemployment rates. By exploring the relationships between these factors, the analysis reveals key insights into how wealth, corruption, and tourism influence a country’s economic health. Objectives include examining how corruption correlates with GDP, how cost of living impacts tourism and unemployment, and ranking countries by overall economic health using a composite index. The project also clusters countries into performance groups, offering a clear comparison framework for economic stability and policy insights.

title: ABOUT
text:
Myself Pooja Sridharan. I am a data-driven professional with over 4 years of diverse experience, including 2 years as a Data Analyst. Currently, I am pursuing a master’s degree in Data Analytics Engineering with a minor in Business Analytics at George Mason University, where I am focusing on enhancing my expertise in data science, machine learning, and marketing analytics.
As a Data Analyst, I have a proven track record of leveraging data to create actionable insights, automate processes, and streamline decision-making. My technical proficiency includes Python, SQL, and advanced visualization tools such as Power BI and Tableau. I have also developed expertise in web scraping, automation, and API integration, which has allowed me to build efficient data pipelines, improve data accuracy, and increase operational efficiency.

title: Data Job Trends Analysis (2020- 2024)
text:
Project Brief
The Data Job Trends Analysis Dashboard (2020-2024) is an interactive Power BI dashboard that analyzes the global demand for data-related roles across different countries from 2020 to 2024. It provides insights into job market fluctuations, highlights country-specific trends, and helps professionals understand the evolving demand for data skills. This tool is essential for data analysts, recruiters, and career strategists aiming to make informed decisions based on recent market data.
